DESCRIPTION OF DAMAGE:
A copper water supply pipe in the second-floor bathroom burst due to freezing temperatures, causing extensive water damage to the following areas:
1. Second floor master bathroom - complete flooding, damaged flooring, vanity, and drywall
2. Second floor hallway - water-stained hardwood floors
3. First floor living room ceiling - water penetration through ceiling, damaged drywall and light fixtures
4. First floor dining room - water damage to hardwood floors and crown molding
5. Basement - water accumulation affecting stored personal property

EMERGENCY MEASURES TAKEN:
- Water supply shut off immediately upon discovery
- ServPro Water Restoration called for emergency extraction (Invoice: $3,200)
- Industrial dehumidifiers and fans placed throughout affected areas
- Temporary tarps placed over damaged ceiling areas

